The reason I have come for a sight test today is because I've noticed my distance vision is no longer as good as it was, and I don't have any glasses for my distance vision. I do however wear glasses for reading. I've been wearing reading glasses for the past 15 years and I can see well with them. I'm not really having any other visual problems!

 My last eye test was on 26/10/2019, but I think my reading glasses are a little older, I can't quite remember.

 For the past year now I've been getting dull headaches, on and off, on the side of my head, around once a week, when doing computer work or reading for long periods of time. Luckily, I don't get any eyestrain but the headaches are getting annoying.

 I don't get any double vision or floaters but for several years I've been getting flashes in my vision every night, not sure if its happening in both eyes or just one.

 30 years ago I was discharged from the hospital after having cyst removal surgery and being prescribed lid scrubs for my blepharitis, that was the only time I went to the eye hospital. It was an eye opening experience.

 My family don't have any eye or health problems, like diabetes or high blood pressure, but my dad did have cataracts.

 My general health is good. I don't have diabetes but I am genetically predisposed to type 2 diabetes, and my last medical exam was 2 months ago to get my blood sugar levels checked.

I take vitamin D and cod liver oil supplements but no medication. Around May/ June time I may take antihistamines and sometimes steroid drops if my hayfever really flares up. I don't smoke since I know it's damaging to my health.

 I spend about 6 hours a day looking at my computer screen since I'm a teacher. It's easy for me to drive up to the school I work at, sometimes I even motorcycle which I really enjoy, as well as climbing on the weekends!
